            The digital epidemic killing Indians
            Smart phones are making it easier for millions of Indians to communicate and share messages on social media. But misinformation is spreading fast and can often turn deadly. This is one such story.Video by Varun Nayar and Kunal SehgalThis story is part of a series by the BBC on disinformation and fake news - a global problem challenging the way we share information and perceive the world around us.To see more stories and learn more about the series visit www.bbc.co.uk/fakenews
                
                        12 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
